main event: A witness observed a round object, the size of a dime held at arm's length, which was white with a red dot in the middle, at an elevation of 30 degrees in the southeast.
interesting points: The object was visible for thirty minutes through 6X binoculars., The sighting occurred at GMT 21/0255Z on June 20, 1956., The object's movement was described as moving back and forth across the sky., The object was possibly caused by the planet Saturn, which was located in the southeast at that time., The report was unclassified and sent to various military departments.
sighted object: one round object, white with red dot
witness description: The witness was out with his girlfriend looking at the stars.
